The paper describes a novel deep network architecture for supervised learning, which involves sparse coding and multilevel optimization. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, given that the paper focuses on image classification tasks and uses convolutional layers, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.LG and cs.NE.
